# YouTube Data API v3 keys for the in-room search + now-playing meta.
# These ship in the client bundle (NEXT_PUBLIC_*), so:
#   1. Restrict each key to your origins in Google Cloud Console
#      (e.g. http://localhost:3000, https://your-prod-domain.com).
#   2. Never reuse them for backend secrets.
#
# Numbered convention: the client picks up every NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY_<n>
# it can find, sorted by <n>. Normal traffic uses key #1 until it hits
# `quotaExceeded`, then transparently advances to key #2, and so on.
# Add more keys to expand daily capacity — no code change needed.
NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY_1=your-first-youtube-data-api-key
# NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY_2=your-second-key-when-you-have-one
# NEXT_PUBLIC_YOUTUBE_API_KEY_3=...
